snippet.textDisplay:
This song focused more on experimenting with different instruments and ignored vocal strengths that could have been a powerful tool to bring more appeal. Sadly, I was craving for more vocal minutes.

And I really didn't like the sudden jump to the guitars at the beginning. For me, it didn't blend as it should have been.

The song felt good for a moment at mid section, and the ending felt good as well.

I won't say it's a total abomination. Coke studio is all about experimenting with something new. Unlike the previous ones, this one flopped, at least to me.

No hatred towards anyone involved with this.
